channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Letter From RI School of Design President to Occupying Protesters Is Something Else—So Is the Result
Clarence Thomas says he receives 'nastiness' from critics, describes D.C. as a 'hideous place'
item.description: Supreme Court Justice Clarence Thomas said he and his wife have faced "nastiness" and "lies" in recent years and criticized Washington, D.C., as a "hideous place."

item.title: Rep. Waltz to Newsmax: Biden Aid Threat 'About Winning Michigan'
item.description: Rep. Mike Waltz, R-Fla., told Newsmax on Friday that President Joe Biden's threat to withhold military aid from Israel "is about winning Michigan."

item.title: Feel-Good Friday: NICU Nurses Taylor and Drew Deras Foster, Then Adopt the Baby They Nursed Back to Life
Court rules Pennsylvania borough ordinance cracking down on lawn signs is unconstitutional
item.description: A federal appeals court has ruled against a Camp Hill, Pennsylvania, ordinance aimed at cutting down on the abundance of political lawn signs.

item.title: Billy Graham Statue for US Capitol to Be Unveiled Next Week
item.description: A statue of the late Rev. Billy Graham set to stand inside the U.S. Capitol to represent North Carolina will be unveiled next week in a ceremony.House Speaker Mike Johnson, other congressional members and the family of the Charlotte-born evangelist are expected to attend...

item.title: WATCH: ABC News Whines About Use of 'Chemical Irritant' Against Pro-Hamas Mob Trying to Wreck Graduation
Kansas bill cracking down on foreign land ownership vetoed by Democratic governor
item.description: Democratic Kansas Gov. Laura Kelly on Friday vetoed a bill limiting foreign land ownership, in a move Republicans castigated as apathetic toward national security threats.

item.title: Sen. Van Hollen: US' Israel War Report 'Inadequate'
item.description: Sen. Chris Van Hollen, D-Md., told reporters on Friday that the Biden administration's report on Israel's war conduct of the war in Gaza is "woefully inadequate," The Hill reported.

item.title: Judge Merchan Tells Michael Cohen to Zip It—Stop Yapping About the Trump Trial
Budget leaders reach deal with Youngkin on Virginia spending plan
item.description: Virginia budget negotiators have reportedly reached a compromise with Republican Gov. Glenn Youngkin on the Old Dominion's next two-year spending plan.

item.title: Rep. Cline to Newsmax: Judiciary Panel Wants Nathan Wade to Testify
item.description: Rep. Ben Cline, R-Va., told Newsmax the House Judiciary Committee, on which he sits, is eager to hear from Nathan Wade, the former lead prosecutor in Democrat Fulton County, Georgia, DA Fani Willis' 2020 election interference case against Donald Trump.

item.title: Target Is Pulling Back on Pride-Themed Products in Its Stores. The Reason Why Is Obvious.
Disney heiress goes after 'potential Trump VP' Kristi Noem with 'Old Yeller' comparison
item.description: The grandniece of Walt Disney evoked the class Disney movie, Old Yeller, in a plea to reject Republicans after Kristi Noem's book detailed the killing of the family's ranch dog.

item.title: Justice Thomas Says Critics Push 'Nastiness,' Calls D.C. a 'Hideous Place'
item.description: Supreme Court Justice Clarence Thomas told attendees at a judicial conference Friday that he and his wife have faced "nastiness" and "lies" over the last several years and decried Washington, D.C., as a "hideous place."Thomas spoke at a conference attended by judges,...
